The International Space Station (ISS) was forced to dodge a deadly field of space junk last week after debris came within 1,000 feet (0.3km) of its orbit.

On Thursday, the Expedition 39 astronauts raised the altitude of the ISS by half a mile (0.8km) to prevent a Gravity-style disaster.

Nasa said the astronauts fired 53 thrusters at on the ISS’ Zvezda Service Module for three minutes, 40 seconds to complete the manoeuvre.

