This was enough to prevent the space station from colliding with parts of an old Ariane 5 rocket which was launched by the European Space Station.

This is the second time in less than three weeks that the ISS has had to sidestep space junk.

Nasa spokesman Kelly Humphries said the space agency has had to consider sidestepping space junk dozens of times since the outpost was launched in 1998, sometimes cancelling the orbital dodge at the last moment.

