As well as this, there are many millions of pieces of debris that are so small they can’t be tracked.

Even tiny paint flecks can damage a spacecraft when travelling at these velocities.

A number of space shuttle windows have had to be replaced because of damage caused by material that was analysed and shown to be paint flecks.

‘The greatest risk to space missions comes from non-trackable debris,’ said Nicholas Johnson, Nasa chief scientist for orbital debris.

